                            <title>Page Added : SAKDEV:Partial sakai builds</title>
                        <link>http://bugs.sakaiproject.org/confluence/display/SAKDEV/Partial+sakai+builds</link>
            <description><![CDATA[
                
<p>In order to enable partial builds of sakai using maven, you need to run the following command. The version at the end should match the current version you are building:</p>
<div class="code"><div class="codeContent">
<pre class="code-xml">maven plugin:download -DgroupId=sakaiproject -DartifactId=sakai -Dversion=2.0.1</pre>
</div></div>

<p>To do a full build "maven sakai", or "maven cln bld" from the source root.<br/>
For a quick full build, do "maven bld". Not doing "cln" makes it run faster.</p>

<p>With the partial build plugin (after you have done at least ONE complete full build) you can then cd to a module within Sakai and build there (maven bld).</p>

<p>The deploy stage (maven dpl) relies on the maven project information, so if you do that from a module, only that module will deploy.</p>

<p>Read about Sakai and maven from the official Sakai documentation on Sakai Collab in the Sakai Development site:<br/>
<span class="nobr"><a href="http://collab.sakaiproject.org/access/content/group/1097928811887-22636/Architecture%20Docs/Sakai%202/sakai_maven.pdf" title="Visit page outside Confluence" rel="nofollow">http://collab.sakaiproject.org/access/content/group/1097928811887-22636/Architecture%20Docs/Sakai%202/sakai_maven.pdf<sup><img class="rendericon" src="/confluence/images/icons/linkext7.gif" height="7" width="7" align="absmiddle" alt="" border="0"/></sup></a></span></p>
            ]]></description>
        </item>
            <item>
                            <title>Page Added : SAKDEV:Adding permissions to Sakai</title>
                        <link>http://bugs.sakaiproject.org/confluence/display/SAKDEV/Adding+permissions+to+Sakai</link>
            <description><![CDATA[
                
<p>To add a permission to the list of possible permissions in sakai, simply add it to the end of legacy/component/src/config/registration.xml</p>

<p>For example, for melete we add the following two:</p>
<div class="code"><div class="codeContent">
<pre class="code-xml"><span class="code-tag">&lt;function name=<span class="code-quote">"melete.author"</span> /&gt;</span>
<span class="code-tag">&lt;function name=<span class="code-quote">"melete.student"</span> /&gt;</span></pre>
</div></div>

<p>You can find the default list of Sakai permissions here:<br/>
<a href="/confluence/display/ENC/Permissions+list" title="Permissions list">Sakai Permissions List</a></p>
            ]]></description>
        </item>
            <item>
                            <title>Page Added : SAKDEV:Virginia Tech Sakai Quick Deployment Notes</title>
                        <link>http://bugs.sakaiproject.org/confluence/display/SAKDEV/Virginia+Tech+Sakai+Quick+Deployment+Notes</link>
            <description><![CDATA[
                
<p>The quick deployment notes from Virginia Tech:<br/>
(Sakai 2.0.1 rc2, Hardware load balancer, Custom LDAP, Oracle, Melete)</p>
<ol>
	<li>Deploy a JDK installation (1.4.2)</li>
	<li>Install maven, edit ~/build.properties in the home directory of the user that compiles sakai like so:<br/>
	<b>Note: Trailing slash on maven.tomcat.home is CRITICAL</b>
<div class="code"><div class="codeContent">
<pre class="code-xml">maven.tomcat.home = /apps/tomcat/sakai/
maven.repo.remote = http://www.ibiblio.org/maven/,http://cvs.sakaiproject.org/maven/</pre>
</div></div></li>
	<li>Create or symlink /var/melete, /var/meleteDocs, and /var/uploads for Melete</li>
	<li>Install subversion, put SUBVERSION_HOME/bin in your path</li>
	<li>Get sakai source (<span class="nobr"><a href="https://source.sakaiproject.org/svn/" title="Visit page outside Confluence" rel="nofollow">https://source.sakaiproject.org/svn/<sup><img class="rendericon" src="/confluence/images/icons/linkext7.gif" height="7" width="7" align="absmiddle" alt="" border="0"/></sup></a></span>)</li>
	<li>Optional: Apply any patches required by your site (<span class="nobr"><a href="https://source.sakaiproject.org/contrib/" title="Visit page outside Confluence" rel="nofollow">https://source.sakaiproject.org/contrib/<sup><img class="rendericon" src="/confluence/images/icons/linkext7.gif" height="7" width="7" align="absmiddle" alt="" border="0"/></sup></a></span>)</li>
	<li>Make any edits required by packages like melete (check the docs included with Melete)</li>
	<li>Add/Setup site user provider (<a href="/confluence/display/ENTR/UserDirectoryProvider" title="UserDirectoryProvider">ENTR:UserDirectoryProvider</a>)</li>
	<li>Run "maven sakai" in sakai directory</li>
	<li>Edit sakai.properties and placeholder.properties in TOMCAT_HOME/sakai/</li>
	<li>Start server (TOMCAT_HOME/bin/startup.sh)</li>
</ol>

            ]]></description>
