                            <title>Page Added : SAKDEV:Sakai Implementor Call-in, Aug-Sep 2005, Monday's 2 PM EDT</title>
                        <link>http://bugs.sakaiproject.org/confluence/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=6373</link>
            <description><![CDATA[
                
<p>As a supplement to the Sakai-Dev developer meetings and our daily email exchanges I've scheduled a series of call-in conference calls intended to support developers et al who have upcoming production/pilot releases this fall.  Jon Anderson, Zhen Qian, myself and others will be available to field questions and help support those preparing to deploy Sakai. Others who would like to join the conversation and help field questions are welcome to do so (send me an email and let me know that you are interested in helping out).</p>

<p>We'll start with an informal call-in format.  Future calls could focus on specific topics if people deem it helpful.  Feel free to suggest topics or areas worth discussing (I can then work to line up experts who could join in the calls to answer targeted questions).</p>

<p>The call-ins are scheduled for Mondays at 2 PM - 3:30 PM EDT for the next several weeks.</p>

<p>Schedule<br/>
Mon., 8 Aug. 2:00 PM EDT<br/>
Mon., 15 Aug. 2:00 PM EDT<br/>
Mon., 22 Aug. 2:00 PM EDT<br/>
Mon., 29 Aug. 2:00 PM EDT<br/>
Wed. 7 Sep. (Monday is a holiday in these parts)<br/>
Mon., 12 Sep. 2:00 PM EDT<br/>
Mon., 19. Sep. 2:00 PM EDT</p>

<p>(11 AM in Berkeley, 1 PM at IU, 7 PM in Cambridge, England, 8 PM in Copenhagen, Denmark and Cape Town, South Africa)<br/>
 <br/>
Dial in number <br/>
734-615-6802</p>

<p>Pass code  <br/>
6710</p>
